<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,223,682]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,338,439,465]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Comments:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Bocage" baseAuthorityYear="1867" box="[343,558,439,465]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Meroles" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="reticulatus">
<emphasis box="[343,558,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Meroles reticulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a species known from the coastal regions of the Namib desert in southwestern 
<collectingCountry box="[151,233,475,501]" name="Angola" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Angola</collectingCountry>
and northern 
<collectingCountry box="[390,486,475,501]" name="Namibia" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Namibia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Marques, M. P. &amp; Ceriaco, L. M. P. &amp; Blackburn, D. C. &amp; Bauer, A. M." box="[500,731,475,501]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="1 - 501" refId="ref38562" refString="Marques, M. P., Ceriaco, L. M. P., Blackburn, D. C. &amp; Bauer, A. M. (2018) Diversity and distribution of the amphibians and terrestrial reptiles of Angola atlas of historical and bibliographic records (1840 - 2017). Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences, Series 4, 65 (Supplement 2), 1 - 501." type="journal article" year="2018">
Marques 
<emphasis box="[607,663,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
). Like 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Bocage" baseAuthorityYear="1867" box="[807,954,475,501]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Meroles" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="anchietae">
<emphasis box="[807,954,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">M. anchietae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, there are very few published records from 
<collectingCountry box="[151,236,511,537]" name="Angola" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Angola</collectingCountry>
, although there are several specimens present in natural history museums’ collections (
<bibRefCitation author="Ceriaco, L. M. P. &amp; De Sa, S. A. C. &amp; Bandeira, S. &amp; Valerio, H. &amp; Stanley, E. L. &amp; Kuhn, A. L. &amp; Marques, M. P. &amp; Vindum, J. V. &amp; Blackburn, D. C. &amp; Bauer, A. M." box="[1203,1432,511,537]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="15 - 61" refId="ref35490" refString="Ceriaco, L. M. P., De Sa, S. A. C., Bandeira, S., Valerio, H., Stanley, E. L., Kuhn, A. L., Marques, M. P., Vindum, J. V., Blackburn, D. C. &amp; Bauer, A. M. (2016 a) Herpetological survey of the Iona National Park and Namibe National Park, Angola, with a synoptic list of the amphibians and reptiles of Namibe Province, southwestern Angola. Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences, Series 4, 63 (2), 15 - 61." type="journal article" year="2016">
Ceríaco 
<emphasis box="[1298,1354,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">et al.</emphasis>
2016a
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Marques, M. P. &amp; Ceriaco, L. M. P. &amp; Blackburn, D. C. &amp; Bauer, A. M." box="[151,384,547,574]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="1 - 501" refId="ref38562" refString="Marques, M. P., Ceriaco, L. M. P., Blackburn, D. C. &amp; Bauer, A. M. (2018) Diversity and distribution of the amphibians and terrestrial reptiles of Angola atlas of historical and bibliographic records (1840 - 2017). Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences, Series 4, 65 (Supplement 2), 1 - 501." type="journal article" year="2018">
Marques 
<emphasis box="[257,315,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
). Specimens MHNCUP/REP 229–230 are the first published records for “Bahia dos Tigres”. Ferreira did not publish these specimens, but identified them as “ 
<taxonomicName box="[911,1150,583,609]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Scapateira" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="reticulata">
<emphasis box="[911,1150,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Scapateira reticulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
”, as noted by the extant labels. The species was recently collected by Luís M. P. Ceríaco and Mariana P. Marques in the same area where Newton collected the aforementioned specimens (
<figureCitation box="[711,779,655,681]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="20.[151,250,1989,2013]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,1107,1963]" captionTargetId="figure-52@20.[151,1436,1107,1963]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 8. Life photo of Meroles reticulatus from Baía dos Tigres. Photo by Luis Ceríaco." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5453983" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5453983/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
